# Agent Execution & Token Efficiency Rules

- **Strict Conciseness**: Skip long internal self-contradictory debates, pre-plan recaps, or repetitive summaries. Think quietly.
- **Action-Oriented Planning**: When working in Agent/Composer mode, limit structural plan proposals to a maximum of 3-5 concise bullet points before executing file changes.
- **No Redundant Snippets**: Never print out entire unchanged code blocks or files in the chat panel. Only show or discuss targeted lines being modified.
- **Analyze Thoroughly First**: Read the target files fully _once_ to establish a unified plan rather than making blind trial-and-error edits that trigger expensive context loops.
